# Mobile UI Design Patterns

## Mobile-First Approach

Always design for mobile first, then enhance for desktop.

### Breakpoint Strategy

Use single breakpoint at 600px:

```css
/* Default: Desktop styles */

@media (max-width: 600px) {
    /* Mobile overrides */
}
```

## Mobile Size Guidelines

From [public/styles.css](mdc:public/styles.css):

```css
@media (max-width: 600px) {
    body {
        padding: 8px;
        padding-top: 15px;
    }
    
    .card {
        padding: 18px 15px;
        border-radius: 10px;
    }
    
    h1 {
        font-size: 19px; /* Compact title */
        margin-bottom: 18px;
    }
    
    h2 {
        font-size: 16px;
        margin-bottom: 15px;
    }
    
    /* Toggle switch - compact */
    .switch {
        width: 80px;
        height: 40px;
    }
    
    /* Form controls - compact */
    .select-input {
        padding: 10px;
        font-size: 14px;
    }
    
    .btn {
        padding: 12px 16px;
        font-size: 14px;
    }
}
```

## Disabled State Styling

Provide clear visual feedback for disabled controls:

```css
.btn:disabled {
    background: #cbd5e0;
    color: #a0aec0;
    cursor: not-allowed;
    opacity: 0.6;
    transform: none;
    box-shadow: none;
}

.select-input:disabled {
    background: #edf2f7;
    color: #a0aec0;
    cursor: not-allowed;
    opacity: 0.6;
}
```

## Loading State - Consolidated Box

Use status box for loading animations to prevent UI jumping:

```css
.arduino-status {
    padding: 15px;
    background: #f7fafc;
    border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
}

.arduino-status.waiting {
    background: #ebf8ff; /* Blue tint */
    border: 2px solid #4299e1;
}

.loading-spinner-inline {
    width: 16px;
    height: 16px;
    border: 3px solid #bee3f8;
    border-top: 3px solid #3182ce;
    border-radius: 50%;
    animation: spin 1s linear infinite;
}
```

